  "title": "TECHNICAN / SENIOR TECHNICIAN",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements : <br /><br />Job Description and Requirements : <br /><u><strong>Job Description :</strong></u> <br /><br />We are an established engineering system integrator looking for a skilled technician like you to bring expertise to our team.<br />Your primary role is to provide high quality, cost effective repair services and technical support to our valued air technology users.<br />You will work closely with our service, engineering and project teams in implementing this strategy.<br /><br /><u><strong>Responsibilities : </strong></u><br />- Troubleshooting and repair of mechanical and electrical equipment such as vacuum pumps, compressors, control panels, sensors etc.<br />-Running and interpreting QC tests results and make diagnostic recommendations<br />- Assist in preparation of service and safety documentation including Work Permits, Safe Work Procedures, Method of Statement, Risk Assessments and Service Reports<br />- Keeping abreast of advancements in your field, attending courses and workshops as required<br />- Build and maintain strong relationships with customers<br />- Work closely together with other technicians /engineers as a team in projects and site work<br /><br /><u><strong>Requirements : </strong></u><br />-Minimum higher NITEC/ITE qualification in Electrical or Mechanical Engineering<br />- At least 2 years experience in servicing and repair of  facilities equipment. Experience in control panels, PLC, lo T, vacuum pumps, compressors and diaphragm pumps is an important plus<br />- Working knowledge in control panel electrical circuits & troubleshooting, Instrument circuit drawings, understand pumps construction drawings and MOM safety regulations.<br />- Good interpersonal and communication skills<br />-Able to work with others in a team<br />-Self motivated and result orientated<br />-Shows initiative and eagerness for self-improvement</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
